column1: Support Portal application removal/Retirement
column33:
As we transition our organizational management to MDM, we plan to remove the support portal applications in Cert and Prod.

Please follow the steps below: Test it in Cert first before making the changes in Production.

# Remove the support portal war files from the TC ePCAdmin server.
#* HMHVPC01-TCK6PRODADMINAPP
#* HMHVPC01-TCK6CERTADMINAPP
# Supportportal DB backup/ removal - Coordinate with BSD DBA.
#* CERT DB: jdbc:oracle:thin:thin@10.34.36.91.com:1521/*SPTEST*
#* PROD DB:jdbc:oracle:thin:@db.prod.clm.app.hmhco.com:1521/*PSUPP01*
# Archive the below support portal repo and make sure that the repo is removed from SNYK.
#* [https://scm.eng.hmhco.com/Mature-Platforms/supportportal|https://scm.eng.hmhco.com/Mature-Platforms/supportportal]
#* [https://scm.eng.hmhco.com/Mature-Platforms/supportportal_BVT|https://scm.eng.hmhco.com/Mature-Platforms/supportportal_BVT]



*Production*: [http://hmhsupportportal.thinkcentral.com/supportPortalWeb/start.do|http://hmhsupportportal.thinkcentral.com/supportPortalWeb/start.do]

*Cert*: [http://hmhsupportportal-cert.thinkcentral.com/supportPortalWeb/start.do|http://hmhsupportportal-cert.thinkcentral.com/supportPortalWeb/start.do]

*Note*: We got the go-ahead from the order management team.

column1: Health-check and Monitoring - September 2025
column33:
TCK Application Monitoring on daily basis for BTS 2025.

|Date|Date of health-check|
|CF Stack CPU & Memory usage|review CPU and Memory usage for previous Day and update|

|Admin Stack CPU & Memory usage|review CPU and Memory usage for previous Day and update|
|NGINX ELB CPU & Memory usage|review CPU and Memory usage for previous Day and update|
|DB Server CPU/Memory|review CPU and Memory usage for previous Day and update|
|DB AWR report|review DB AWR report for previous Day and update|
|Space Availability|Review /location & /root space availability and update|
|User Logged in|Number of users logged previous day|
|Distinct User Logged in|Number of users logged previous day|
|Users Created|Number of users Created previous day|
|Peak usage|maximum concurrent user logged in previous day|

column1: INT | Assignment Service and ActiveMQ Server Termination
column33:
*Description:*

This ticket outlines the plan to terminate the Assignment Service and ActiveMQ servers in the INT Environment due to security vulnerabilities.

* The INT Assignment Service and ActiveMQ servers are planned for termination, as CERT servers are primarily used for validations.
* Infosec reported vulnerabilities in the Assignment Service/ActiveMQ servers, with the following count:

|HMHDEVVPC01-ASMTINTAMQ|70584|
|HMHDEVVPC01-ASMTINTAPP|5754|

column1: Reporting Service Retirement
column33:
*Reporting Service* - Quick Reports - only used for Player-enabled products. *Doesn't have any dedicated DB, it fetches the data from the TC/HMO database via DB views.* Provides information (rates) on the performance of certain assignments, students and classes. This information is used by HMH Player.

+*Actions:*+

* Establish if these services can be retired (please add usage data)
* Delete old snapshots to free up diskspace
* Shutdown APP server/instances (No DB servers).
* Clear/remove AMI’s and security related tasks.
* Github Repository Archival
* Disable synk scan for Reporting Service

column1: L2 Task | FLT & FLC eGoods Order Detail reports
column33:
This is a weekly activity done (updated *every Wednesday*) for the month of *April, May and June 2025* by L2 team, the ask is to include FLT and FLC eGoods too on the report going forth. For reference [ISR-11330]

There is a manual job done weekly to drop an extract of CLM order details into the above Box location.

Here is the file for *April* /25: [https://hmhco.box.com/s/ri868p9vt4vqm5c7minia7kk7hjjw5ht|https://hmhco.box.com/s/rhos3vaxwb4r6oejdmwcdmaznyg29fyz]

It appears the pull does not yet include orders for Flight products, which are eGood FLT & FLC. 

Can we add files to the pull, for Flight products. 

Also, It is good to keep this query page up to date: [https://scm.eng.hmhco.com/Ed-Core/clm-oac/wiki/Weekly-Reports|https://scm.eng.hmhco.com/Ed-Core/clm-oac/wiki/Weekly-Reports] Thank you!

Box location: [https://hmhco.box.com/s/rhos3vaxwb4r6oejdmwcdmaznyg29fyz|https://hmhco.box.com/s/rhos3vaxwb4r6oejdmwcdmaznyg29fyz]

column1: 2025 | TC PROD Import failure analysis
column33:
*Add Import failure analysis for the year 2025.*

* Import failure is notified to the team via Outlook emails from Oracle “*TCK-Purge/Import Jobs Status*” daily. 
* In case of failure, Dev team investigates the logs and provides DB scripts to fix the import failure/error.
* This is done daily to avoid the issues being reported by Customer as a CSI.

On Checking the package *ELSVC.HC_IDM_IMPORT* and executing the query at line *4637* we found the presence of duplicate users within the same school.

{noformat}SELECT U.user_id
                  FROM   users U,
                         user_profile UP,
                        elsvc.idm_batch_import_details
                  WHERE  idm_batch_import_details.username = U.username
                  AND    idm_batch_import_details.school_pid = UP.organization_id
                  AND    UP.user_id = U.user_id
                  AND    UP.role_id = 'TEACHER'
				  AND    idm_batch_import_details.action = 'U'
                  and batch_import_id = '2ff73916-9629-4fa3-9f05-9a0fe8ff1904';{noformat}

The reported *PID 12179819* was a Cross reference for the organization *Pansophic Learning Accel Schs (88702502)* and we could find the presence of duplicate teacher user [kcarr@accelschools.com|mailto:kcarr@accelschools.com] mapped within same school PID *12162593*.

{noformat}SELECT * FROM (
  SELECT
    u.user_id, u.organization_id, u.username, up.role_id, up.status_flag, up.is_moved,
    to_char(u.create_date, 'dd-MON-yyyy hh24:mi:ss') AS user_create_date,
    count(u.username) OVER (PARTITION BY u.organization_id, u.username) user_count
  FROM
    elsvc.users u, elsvc.user_profile up
  WHERE u.user_id = up.user_id AND u.organization_id IN 
  (SELECT pid FROM elsvc.ORGANIZATION WHERE distpid = '88702502')
)
WHERE user_count > 1
ORDER BY username;{noformat}

column1: Quarterly Analytics | Mature platform Unique Login count
column33:
Tim Nolan reached out to us requesting for the Unique users login count for the quarter for both TC and HMOF.

We will maintain "[TIM_Quaterly_unique_logins|https://hmhco.app.box.com/file/1706677950648]" file in box, which will be updated on quarterly basis for Analytics purpose. Tim can fetch the Unique Login counts for both TC & HMO every quarter from this file.

 

Additionally, the monthly count for both the applications is available in the following box links.

TC: [https://hmhco.app.box.com/file/760317010045?s=8rzxqim1yyszkexyypxsnrkllaym1nof]

HMO: [https://hmhco.app.box.com/file/859755143885?s=s7rjgxjcr7ux2sepb7rotfv1xf5p569a]

 

{*}Definition{*}: 

*Total number of unique logins –* Under this metric if the same user logs in 50 times a day, they will be counted once. However, the same user is counted as unique every day.

*Total number of logins –* All logins to a platform in a month. Counts multiple logins for the users in a day. (eg: if user A logs in 5 times a day, the login count will be 5 for that user).

 

{*}ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA{*}:
 * extract the reports for TC and HMO
 * report should include unique logins for the requested quarter (i.e 3 months).
 * each user is counted once only for the 90 day period.

 

{color:#de350b}*Note: We do not have the count of Licenses, that is out of scope for Platform teams.*{color}

column1: ODMS - Address Remaining Critical & High Vulnerabilities
column33:
This ticket is created to track and address the remaining critical and high vulnerabilities identified in the ODMS application after the earlier ticket, which covered vulnerabilities of the Non-Prod environment and backup images.

Currently, we are in the process of procuring an SSL certificate to be configured at the Load Balancer (LB) for the new Production environment. This step is part of the ongoing migration of the Production server from Windows Server 2012R2 to Windows Server 2022.

The completion of the SSL configuration and migration activities is expected to resolve the majority of the outstanding vulnerabilities in the ODMS Production environment.
column429:
* SSL certificate procured and installed successfully at LB for new Prod.
* Production environment migrated to Windows Server 2022.
* All critical and high vulnerabilities for ODMS Prod re-evaluated and confirmed as resolved or mitigated.

column1: Entitlements data for TC & HMO
column33:
We are looking for entitlements data for TC & HMO, as part of discussions with stakeholders on possible sunset of the legacy apps.

Is it possible to have a separate column for schools & Districts please?

We need this data to give a true reflection of entitlements i.e:

* districts buy one program, and if there are multiple subscriptions for same ISBN, with overlapping dates, then include only the one with the latest expiry date (furthest into the future).
* and do not have the same ISBN appear more than once for the same district.
* If we cannot tell which program they bought the ISBN under, then we can make a ‘best guess’ from the State value for the District e.g. if they are in CA, then we assume CA Journeys.

Please exclude test and eval districts.
column2745:
24/Oct/25 9:23 AM;5aa6695234e1832140816c8e;Hi [~accountid:712020:dbf0b704-700b-4a7e-8673-f6b5df51e371] ,

Please find below the HMO and TCK Active Entitlements as of today.

[^TCK_Active_Entitlement_14910.xlsx]
[^HMO_Active_Entitlements_14910.xlsx]

Attached below the query used for reference.

*TCK:* 

{noformat}SELECT distinct ORG.PID,
  ORG.NAME,
  ORG.DISTPID,
  ORG.DISTRICT,
  ORG.MSTATE as State,
  HP.ISBN,   
  HP.TITLE,
  HP.GRADE_IDS,
  MAX(OP.SUBSCRIPTION_AVAIL_DATE) as Activation_Date,
  MAX(OP.SUBSCRIPTION_END_DATE) as Expiration_Date
FROM ORG_PRODUCT op,
  HC_PRODUCT hp,
  ELSVC.organization ORG
WHERE op.PRODUCT_ID = hp.PRODUCT_ID
AND op.ORG_ID = ORG.PID
AND OP.SUBSCRIPTION_END_DATE > sysdate
AND ORG.pid NOT LIKE '88z%'
AND ORG.NAME NOT LIKE 'ZZ%'
AND ORG.NAME NOT LIKE 'Z H%'
AND ORG.NAME NOT LIKE 'zz%'
AND ORG.NAME NOT LIKE 'xref%'
AND ORG.NAME NOT LIKE '%HMH%'
GROUP BY ORG.PID, ORG.NAME, ORG.DISTPID, ORG.DISTRICT, ORG.MSTATE, HP.ISBN, HP.TITLE, HP.GRADE_IDS
ORDER BY Expiration_Date desc;{noformat}

*HMO*:

{noformat}SELECT DISTINCT S.PID,
  S.NAME,
  S.DISTPID,
  S.DISTRICT,
  S.MSTATE as State,
  SP.ISBN,
  SP.TITLE,
  SP.STUDENT_EDITION_ISBN,
  Max(HESI.ACTIVATION_DATE) as Activation_Date,
  Max(HESI.EXPIRATION_DATE) as Expiration_Date
FROM LYCEA.HRW_EC_SECURE_ITEM HESI,
  HRW.SECURE_PROGRAMS SP,
  HRW.SCHOOLS S
WHERE HESI.SPROG_ID           = SP.PROG_ID
AND HESI.OWNER_ID             = S.PID 
AND HESI.EXPIRATION_DATE > sysdate
AND S.NAME NOT LIKE 'ZZ%'
AND S.NAME NOT LIKE 'Z H%'
AND S.NAME NOT LIKE 'zz%'
AND S.NAME NOT LIKE 'xref%'
AND S.NAME NOT LIKE '%HMH%' 
GROUP BY S.PID, S.NAME, S.DISTPID, S.DISTRICT,S.MSTATE, SP.ISBN, SP.TITLE, SP.STUDENT_EDITION_ISBN
ORDER BY Expiration_Date desc;{noformat}

Sangeetha R

column1: HMO - Knewton Monthly Product User Counts September 2025
column33:
As a HMH financial representative, I want to assess the number of user activations of Knewton products so that I can calculate users for HMH and Knewton's contractual engagement.

*Acceptance Criteria*
Produce Knewton Product User Counts report with the data that represents the number of real *HMO PROD* users, teachers and students, entitled to Knewton products who logged in between 1st September and 30th September 2025.

The header of the report contains: Report title
Reporting time interval
A sum of: Count of every teacher per Knewton product the teacher is entitled to if the teacher logged into HMO between 1st September and 30th September 2025.

Count of every student per Knewton product assigned to the student's classes if the student logged into HMO between 1st September and 30th September 2025.

There is one count per user per Knewton product and if a user has access to more than one product, they are counted for each product, e.g. 2 products => count the user twice.
Any user who has not logged in between 1st September and 30th September 2025 despite having access to a Knewton product, is not included in the count.

The body of the report contains: Knowledge Graph Id
User Id
Knewton product ISBN
Date of user's last login
Time of user's last login

The data will be tagged with "Teacher" vs "Student"

*Notes:*
Report should be stored in the following location:
[https://hmhco.box.com/s/9tq10mf67uj3ixf420hsq8en7dbpn28z|https://hmhco.box.com/s/9tq10mf67uj3ixf420hsq8en7dbpn28z]
Data set to be pulled from the Platform database for the month just passed.
Test accounts should NOT be included in the dataset.
Delivery format will be a basic MS Excel spreadsheet. See the template attached.
All data to be on one tab

*Background*
HMH Finance request a set of data on a monthly basis of the number of users who have logged in during the previous month and who have access to a Knewton product, i.e. teachers to whom Knewton product/s have been assigned and students who are in a class with a Knewton product (regardless of whether they have used the product or not),
Note: This data is required to assess the number of user activations of Knewton products.

column1: CAS User Data Analysis (2022–2025)
column33:
This ticket is created to gather and document the analysis and statistical state of the CAS database for the years *2022 to 2025*.

We already have detailed CAS user data analysis available through 2021, documented here:  [https://nwea.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/DP2/pages/1200524219/CAS+User+Data+Analysis|https://nwea.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/DP2/pages/1200524219/CAS+User+Data+Analysis|smart-link] 

Required:

* New user Registerations per year by platform and role.
* Count of users last created/Updated an annotation by platform and year of user registration.

Action:

Prepare SQL scripts to extract the required data from the CAS( Datapersistence ) database.

column1: High | Dashboard- SNYK | QS- Prototype Poisoning
column33:
*Snyk Vulnerability Details:*

{color:#172b4d}*Asset name :*{color}{color:#172b4d} Mature-Platforms/dashboard {color}

*Path :* Vulnerability reported in

:‎‎‎Application/HMH.WorkBench.UI/package.json

*Severity :* High

*Introduced through:* application-name@0.0.1 › express@3.0.0-beta7 › connect@2.3.9 › qs@0.4.2

*Fix:* [Upgrade|https://app.snyk.io/org/hmh-tcandhmopmt/fix/73f00338-0f7c-47ce-a4c6-4bafadb7f907?vuln=SNYK-JS-QS-3153490] to express@4.0.0{color:#ffffff}Upgrade to the package.{color}

*Vulnerability Detail :* 
[qs|https://www.npmjs.com/package/qs] is a querystring parser that supports nesting and arrays, with a depth limit.

Affected versions of this package are vulnerable to Prototype Poisoning which allows attackers to cause a Node process to hang, processing an Array object whose prototype has been replaced by one with an excessive length value.

column2762:
18/Nov/25 11:03 PM;712020:a51f8191-37c4-4f60-9ef0-f26299f55162;After Analysis of all the root file of this vulnerability observed that : 

The reported SQL injection finding from Snyk is a *false positive*.

All database queries involved in the Assessments workflow use parameterized SQL via Oracle parameters and a custom SQLBuilder class, and no user-supplied input is ever concatenated into SQL strings.

Snyk traces HTTP parameters (to, from,classname)flowing into:

AssessmentFactory → StrategyFactory → IDbStrategy.Sql → Repo → OracleCommand.CommandText

because snyk cannot analyze our custom sqlbuilder, it assumes SQL is build using concatenation,even though it is not.this results in a false positive.

why this code is safe:

*1.SQL is built using SqlBuilder with parameter placeholders*

*Example :* 

[file:Application/HMH.WorkBench.Platform.Api/HMH.WorkBench.Platform.Api.Basal/DataAccess/Assessments/AssessmentTcTeacher.cs|file:Application/HMH.WorkBench.Platform.Api/HMH.WorkBench.Platform.Api.Basal/DataAccess/Assessments/AssessmentTcTeacher.cs]

Property: Sql

public override string Sql
{
    get
    {
        return new SqlBuilder()
            .Select("ASSIGNED_STUDENTS", "ASSIGNMENT_ID", "ASSIGNMENT_NAME", "CLASSROOM_ID",
                    "CLASSROOM_NAME", "DUEDATE", "FIRSTNAME", "LASTNAME", "STUDENT_ID",
                    "TEACHER_USER_ID", "TEST_SCORE")
            .From("DASHBOARD_ASSESSMENT_SCORE")
            .Where("TEACHER_USER_ID")
            .EqualTo(":TEACHER_USER_ID")   // parameter placeholder, NOT string concatenation
            .OrderBy("DUEDATE desc", "ASSIGNMENT_NAME")
            .ToString();
    }
} 

* -SQL contains parameter markers like: Teacher_USER_ID-
* -No user input is concatenated into SQL text-

*2.User inputs are passed strictly as parameters*

[File:AssessmentTcTeacher.cs|File:AssessmentTcTeacher.cs]

Property: Params

public override Dictionary<string, object> Params
{
    get
    {
        return new Dictionary<string, object>
        {
            { "TEACHER_USER_ID", this.userId }
        };
    }
}

* -Only safe dictionary values-
* -No string concatenation-

*3.Database access uses oracle parameter binding(safe)*

[File:Application/HMH.WorkBench.Platform.Api/HMH.WorkBench.Platform.Api.Basal/DataAccess/Repo.cs|File:Application/HMH.WorkBench.Platform.Api/HMH.WorkBench.Platform.Api.Basal/DataAccess/Repo.cs] 

cmd.CommandText = strategy.Sql;
foreach (var para in strategy.Params)
{
    cmd.Parameters.Add(new OracleParameter(para.Key, para.Value));
}

* -OracleCommand uses parameteried queries-
* -Prevents any SQL injection regardless of input-
* -No raw input ever reaches SQL-

*4*.*HTTP parameters (*{{to}}*,* {{from}}*,* {{className}}*) are used ONLY for in-memory filtering*

They appear only in C# LINQ filters after the SQL query:

var filteredResuls = result.Where(r =>
    (this.to.CompareTo(DateTime.MaxValue) == 0 || r.DueDate <= [this.to|http://this.to]) &&
    (this.from.CompareTo(DateTime.MinValue) == 0 || r.DueDate > this.from) &&
    (string.IsNullOrEmpty(this.className) || this.className == r.ClassRoomName)
).ToList();

* -these values never touch SQL-
* -No SQL injection possible from these inputs.-

Conclusion:

* No SQL concatenation occurs in the codebase.
* All user-supplied values are sent through Oracle parameters.
* {{SqlBuilder}} always produces parameterized SQL.
* Repo binds parameters safely using {{OracleParameter}}.
* The flagged data flow does *not* represent a real SQL injection vector.

*Therefore, this is a false positive and no code change is needed*.

Hi [~accountid:712020:947e03ab-bf6d-4e2a-b0bf-287789ae4ae1]  As per the analysis, can we mark this occurrence as a false positive?

 Thanks

*Snyk Vulnerability Details:*

*Asset name :* Mature-Platforms/contentAPIServices-cas

*Path :* Vulnerability reported in

:TokenGeneration/WebOdata/Scripts/*datajs-1.0.3.js*

*Severity :* High

*Vulnerability :* Insecure Defaults in  project@* › TokenGeneration/WebOdata/Scripts/*datajs-1.0.3.js*

column2751: 16/Jun/25 2:14 AM;712020:a76c41c5-a31f-4548-8c22-27508989206c;I have reverted my changes in develop branch as the new way of fixing this SSRF vulnerability solved the issue partially but not fully , so will try other way to fix this vulnerability.
column2752:
26/Jun/25 1:23 AM;712020:a76c41c5-a31f-4548-8c22-27508989206c;Created sanitizeRequest() function before calling httpClient.request() in invokeRequest() to block internal IPs and strip unsafe headers.

 

request = sanitizeRequest(request);

 

However, *this did not resolve the SSRF issue*, as the root cause lies earlier in the flow — where headers are first set on the request object (e.g., line 593). Sanitizing at invokeRequest is too late since tainted input already flows in.

 

I’ve *reverted the changes* and will now explore applying validation earlier, when the request is first built.
column2753: 08/Jul/25 10:09 PM;712020:a76c41c5-a31f-4548-8c22-27508989206c;The recent SSRF mitigation using *sanitizeRequest() before httpClient.request() didn’t resolve the issue.* Based on the data flow, the vulnerability likely originates earlier in the request lifecycle. I’m *investigating further* and will provide an updated fix soon.

column1: Assessment tab shown ED logo instead of Heinemann
column33:
This issue occurs in test tunnel assessments.

Steps to reproduce- 
 1. Log in as a teacher user.
 2. Launch the DTM / DTMMS product from the product card.
 3. Click on the Assessment in the Table of Contents (TOC).
 4. Open any available assessment.
 5. Observe the behavior in the newly opened tab.

Actual Result- The new tab incorrectly shows the ED logo and title instead of Heinemann.

column33:

This ticket will track the actions taken towards it.

Steps to follow:

* Delete/remove old AMIs and keep only recent AMI 
* Raise a BR ticket to remove/delete the AMIs

column1: Request to move users
column33:
District: Placer co Office of Education
District PID: 00100557
School: PCOE Auburn
School PID: 88780310
Platform: HRW
Customer: Amanda Kilian
Email: akilian@placercoe.org

User(s) affected: All of the teachers and students at the district level.

Issue: All Students Highlighted notes are disappearing until Browser Cache has been cleared
Browser: Google Chrome 141.0.7390.96
Ipad OS: 26.0.1
User(s) Affected:
Isabella Delgado (student2362@ollv.org)
 Kyla Chu (student2486@ollv.org)
Helaina Dorsz (student2589@ollv.org)
Replication Steps:
Impersonate Student student2362@ollv.org
Press Discover
Select program United States History: Civil War to the Present
Select Module 14
Open The Civil Right Movement
Press Notes in the top right
Expected Result: Notes will be saved
Actual Result: Notes are not saved and only appear after clearing cache
Notes:
Director is looking for a permanent solution rather than clearing cache
This is on Google Chrome via iPad
They will not use incognito
They will not provide screenshots
This issue happens intermittently

column1: District missing schools in TC portal.
column33:
PID: 88778393
Issue: District missing schools in TC portal.
User(s) Affected: District

Replication Steps: 
1. Go to ThinkCentral portal (https://www-k6.thinkcentral.com/ePC/start.do)
2. Country: United States 
3. State: North Carolina
- Notice there are two 'Classical Charter Schol of America'

4. Select first Classical Charter Schol of America
- Notice no schools showing.

5. Select second Classical Charter Schol of America
- Notice Classical Charter Schools of Southport and Classical Charter Schools of Wilmington missing.


Troubleshooting done: Able to replicate issue. Confirmed Parent/School org data is correct and synced in IDS/HCP.

District: Classical Charter Schl of America - 88778393

School PIDs: 
- Classical Charter Schools of Leland - 04925878
- Classical Charter Schools of Southport - 12044056
- Classical Charter Schools of Whiteville - 10981006
- Classical Charter Schools of Wilmington - 11931365

Expected Result: For there to be one Classical Charter Schol of America to choose from as a district and for all four schools in district to show as a selectable option in 'School' dropdown list.

Actual Result: There's two districts to choose from with the same name (Classical Charter Schl of America) and Classical Charter Schools of Southport and Classical Charter Schools of Wilmington missing as a selectable option in 'School' dropdown list.

03/Oct/25 3:24 AM;712020:ad7ca951-e27e-4c33-848e-52bf6fa1b3cc;We investigated the CLM DB for the latest processed order for the order numbers *0096271644, 0096271671, 0096273684.* And we can see that the SUBSCRIPTION_END_DATE for these orders is *30-06-26 12:00:00.000000000 AM.* 

But the ISBS’s *'9781328785022', '9781328786838', '9781328694850', '9781328788498', '9781328787828'* which are mentioned in one of the previous comment attached below are the part of order no. *0097192214.*

!Screenshot_1 (1a0f614d-d8e9-4167-913b-9d249ed56531).png|width=200,height=200!


For the above ISBN’s we could see like the *SUBSCRIPTION_END_DATE* is *16-09-25 12:00:00.000000000 AM* in CLM DB.

!image-20251003-102119.png|width=100%,alt="image-20251003-102119.png"!



 As per the functionality any new order will over ride the previous orders.

Hence, the latest order which was processed on *17-09-24* with *Sales Order No. 0097192214 &* *subscription end date* of *16-09-25 will over ride the previous* Order.

User can access products by re-processing the valid and active sales order so the expired ones are over ridden.

column2748: 30/Sep/25 10:02 PM;712020:701f1652-345d-45cc-8921-66a723c5d0bb;Started initial analysis
column2749:
01/Oct/25 2:42 AM;712020:ad7ca951-e27e-4c33-848e-52bf6fa1b3cc;Upon investigating the CLM database, we observed that the latest order was processed on *30-06-2023 at 12:00 AM* with *Sales Order No. 0096745192*. The associated *subscription has an end date* of *30-06-2023 at 12:00 AM*.

This order pertains to the following products:

* *9781328470607* – _Saxon Math Student Edition, Grade 1_
* *9781328470270* – _Saxon Math Teacher Edition, Grade 1_
* *9781328470287* – _Saxon Math Teacher Edition, Grade 2_
* *9781328470614* – _Saxon Math Student Edition, Grade 2_

For reference, please find the attached screenshot.

!image-20251001-092911.png|width=100%,alt="image-20251001-092911.png"!

* These updates are now reflected in the TC platform, causing the resources to appear as *expired* and hence *not visible*.

*Conclusion:*

* This behaviour is *as per design*.
* The TC platform is correctly reflecting the updated subscription end dates from the processed orders. 

*Resolving the ticket* as the system is functioning as expected.
column2750: 01/Oct/25 2:43 AM;712020:ad7ca951-e27e-4c33-848e-52bf6fa1b3cc;Resolving the ticket as per the previous comment.
column2751: 01/Oct/25 4:00 AM;712020:cbb1168a-c517-41b1-925b-3ff13ff06879;Back in support to review and follow up with customer. Pending response or closure.
column2752:
01/Oct/25 4:53 AM;712020:dbf0b704-700b-4a7e-8673-f6b5df51e371;Hi [~accountid:712020:cbb1168a-c517-41b1-925b-3ff13ff06879]  eloborating this, per the functionality any new order will over ride the previous orders.

Hence, the latest order which was processed on *11-04-2022* with *Sales Order No. 0096745192 &* *subscription end date* of *30-06-2023 will over ride the* Order quoted on the CSI “0096598163” which was processed on *31-JUL-21 14:05:33.*

User can access products by re-processing the valid and active sales order so the expired ones are over ridden.

30/Sep/25 8:13 AM;712020:cbb1168a-c517-41b1-925b-3ff13ff06879;Per Customer: Makaio's data continues to be incorrect. He is one of our students on campus who does not participate in any interviews. He has not participate in any interviews this year. As for the other students, interviews are still showing up that they were not administered. 

On a separate note, I have another 3rd grade teacher Elyssa Farmer, that appeared to show 2 interviews given to her entire class. Initially, she did not administer any interviews for the entire class, and data was showing up for each of her students from the previous year. She is the only teacher this happened to where it appears the previous year data transferred. We were not sure what happened but continued to interview her class, in which they have only done one interview but her data is showing both last year and this years data. She also shows up as a student in her data. 

This is not the same issue with Joshua's class, which is showing the exact opposite problem.
column2755:
01/Oct/25 12:20 AM;712020:ce251a5d-ebe0-4951-bb6c-08aca642a1cc;Thank you for the additional clarification.

As per the system’s functionality, the reporting view is designed to show all interviews administered by the class teacher, including those from previous academic years for existing students. For new users, only the current year’s interview data will be displayed.

Based on our validation:

* *Makaio* has completed Interviews 7 and 8, which are correctly reflected in the report. If he was not intended to participate, this may need to be reviewed at the data entry or assignment level.
* The discrepancies observed in *Elyssa Farmer’s* class are consistent with expected behavior for returning students, where previous year data is retained. Her appearance as a student may be due to a role configuration issue .
* *Joshua’s class* shows data aligned with the current year and teacher assignments, and no reporting deviations were found.

CC : [~accountid:712020:dbf0b704-700b-4a7e-8673-f6b5df51e371] [~accountid:5bc9bfb867a5270a3a1c11aa]
column2756: 01/Oct/25 12:21 AM;712020:ce251a5d-ebe0-4951-bb6c-08aca642a1cc;The reporting system is functioning as expected based on the data available. Marking this ticket as resolved based on current validation and expected system behavior. Closing this ticket now. Please feel free to reopen if further assistance is needed or if new issues arise.
column2757: 01/Oct/25 4:02 AM;712020:cbb1168a-c517-41b1-925b-3ff13ff06879;Back in support to review and follow up with customer. Pending response or closure.
column2758: 03/Oct/25 12:42 PM;712020:cbb1168a-c517-41b1-925b-3ff13ff06879;tech is asking the following: curious as to why only the data for one teacher Elyssa Farmer transferred but the rest of the school did not? All of the students are returning students with the exception of a few and those that moved on to middle school
column2759:
06/Oct/25 10:59 PM;712020:ce251a5d-ebe0-4951-bb6c-08aca642a1cc;The reason Elyssa Farmer’s class shows interview data from the previous year while others do not is likely due to how user and class associations were carried over in the system.

If Elyssa retained the same class roster or student associations from the previous academic year, and those students are returning users, their historical interview data would continue to appear in the reporting view. This is expected behavior for returning students and teachers. In contrast, if other teachers had their rosters reset or reassigned for the new year, the system would only show data from the current academic year.

CC: [~accountid:712020:dbf0b704-700b-4a7e-8673-f6b5df51e371] [~accountid:5bc9bfb867a5270a3a1c11aa]
column2760:
06/Oct/25 11:00 PM;712020:ce251a5d-ebe0-4951-bb6c-08aca642a1cc;The reason Elyssa Farmer’s class shows interview data from the previous year while others do not is likely due to how user and class associations were carried over in the system.
If Elyssa retained the same class roster or student associations from the previous academic year, and those students are returning users, their historical interview data would continue to appear in the reporting view. This is expected behavior for returning students and teachers. In contrast, if other teachers had their rosters reset or reassigned for the new year, the system would only show data from the current academic year.

Hope this clarifies the behavior. No further action required at this time—marking this ticket as closed.

column1: Transform Sample Into Lit orders to confirm process
column33:
We have many old/existing Into Lit orders where Into Lit was bundled with another product (e.g. Writable) but were placed before we recognised such kits as Product Bundles.

I have taken 6 orders from 4 customers (all districts) to produce the 6 SQL statement files (1 file per order, updating each affected child line item within each kit of the order), and the Cypher Detach statements (1 detach statement at ed_ref_id level, with the unique set of affected program_codes per org).

The *LIT_Limited_Sample_Orgs_RefIds_ProgramCodes.xslx* file holds the saved program codes per org for all of the affected lines. 

Note, these org’s may well have other Ed material, but this limited update is only targeting Into Lit kits. The orders prepresent all Into Lit kits that have been specified by the business as having a bundle that should migrate to a product bundle entitlement.

Steps:

# Save a copy of the affected SOLI rows before any updates into a temp table
# Update CLM with data extracted from SAP +and+ Insert into Event_Log - see attached 6 “*LIT_SQL*.txt*” files
# Trigger the affected orders to generate OrderCreatedEvent to pass the order data to HCP
# Re-trigger the affected orders to OAC
# Confirm that OrderCreatedEvent got generated
# Confirm OAC was updated
# Perform clean-up OAC to remove the programs without the PBID - one command per org - see “*LIT_Limited_Sample_Detach.txt*” file

column1: PALM Mappings for English IM NL 2025 Into Math v2 (Grades K-A1) with updated titles and added Waggle integration
column33:
h4. The purpose of this ticket is to add Waggle integration to the existing PALM mapping for English Into Math NL 2025 (V2), i.e. it is an update of the most recent mapping at [https://nwea.atlassian.net/issues/AR-3982|https://nwea.atlassian.net/issues/AR-3982]

The following changes have been made:

1. “standard mappings” sheet, column J, and “program details” sheet, column B: customer facing names have been updated

2. “integrations mappings” sheet: Waggle details have been added

h4. The updated PALM mapping file is attached here.


_Fill out the attached example mapping template with all the information requested, there is one line per ISBN._

_The PHL5 code is available from the SAP explorer page in PMC._

_State indicator for California is "California"_

_If any integrations are to be added to the program, please explicitly state them in the ticket as they will not be added otherwise._

_If there is a specific date that this is required for, please note in the ticket or if there are any priority items but note that there is up to a 2 week turnaround for adding mappings._

h4. _N.B. this task sample can only be used for programs that are uniquely and unambiguously identified by the combination of PHL5, state_indicator, beginning-grade, ending-grade and language. For any programs falling outside of that, we need a file that links the individual isbns to the correct programs._
